==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[Antonius]], most likely of unknown Etruscan origin. Latin [[Antonius]], name of a Roman gens (with excrescent -h- probably suggested by the many Greek loan words beginning anth-, e.g., [[άνθος]] "flower", [[άνθρωπος]] "man"). The Roman clan name is of uncertain etymology, but is not Greek or Hebrew.

===Proper noun===
'''Anthony'''

# male given name

